        <div class="section-head">
          <div class="section-head__eyebrow"><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> The Origin</div>
          <h2 class="section-head__title">Why Freshman Finance?</h2>
          <span class="section-head__line"></span>
        </div>
        <p>Nobody teaches you money in school. You graduate, get your first real income, and suddenly you're expected to know what a Roth IRA is, whether you should pay off debt or invest, and how to not blow your whole paycheck in two days.</p>
        <p>Freshman Finance exists because that gap is real — and it's expensive. The goal is simple: break down money topics into plain language, give you the information you actually need, and help you build a foundation before the stakes get higher.</p>
        <p>This is advice from someone in the thick of it — not a financial institution, not a hedge fund manager. Just someone figuring it out and sharing what works.</p>
        <div class="about-values">
          <div class="about-value">
            <div class="about-value__title">No Jargon</div>
            <div class="about-value__text">Plain language only. If it needs a glossary, we'll explain it first.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-value">
            <div class="about-value__title">Student-First</div>
            <div class="about-value__text">Built for people who are new to this, not people who already know it all.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-value">
            <div class="about-value__title">Practical</div>
            <div class="about-value__text">Every piece of content has a clear takeaway you can act on.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-value">
            <div class="about-value__title">Honest</div>
            <div class="about-value__text">No get-rich-quick promises. Just real, sustainable financial habits.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

